audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:10:| BL-001 | Lazy lender storage is safe until touched | `updatePositionView`, `withdraw`, `take` | Realize loss, leave lender stale, force a different state-sensitive action before lender touch | Lender | Effective claim and later action agree | Direct sync already covered; need material branch | `PoC_Blackbox_DeferredPositionUpdate.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:11:| BL-002 | Social loss equals unrecoverable debt | `liquidate` | Partial liquidation, collateral change, then zero-input realization | Lenders | `badDebt <= economically unrecoverable debt` | Duplicate if only zero oracle | `PoC_Blackbox_BadDebtRecoverability.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:12:| BL-003 | Bundle max spend bounds the whole economic action | `buyWithUnitsTargetAndWithdrawCollateral` | Use valid fallback legs and collateral withdrawal in one route | Delegated taker | Spend and collateral effects match intent | Invalid if taker explicitly authorized all effects | `PoC_Blackbox_UserIntentBundle.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:13:| BL-004 | Bundle min receive captures borrower outcome | `supplyCollateralAndSellWithAssetsTarget` | Choose fallback offers with materially different debt units while receive target holds | Borrower | Debt opened is bounded by `maxUnits` | Likely defended by `maxUnits` | Route permutation test |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:14:| BL-005 | Repay bundle fee is understood as separate from debt repayment | `repayAndWithdrawCollateral` | Relayer chooses referral pct and receiver while operating for authorized borrower | Borrower | Authorized repay cannot redirect unrelated value | Broad delegate may make intended | Authorization-scope PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:15:| BL-006 | A maker group represents one economic offer family | `consumed`, `setConsumed` | Reuse same group across opposite sides or loan tokens | Maker | Shared cap semantics match signed intent | Docs warn same direction/token; likely user error | Mixed-family group PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:16:| BL-007 | A lender can rely on withdrawable backing after repayment | `repay`, `withdraw`, `claimSettlementFee` | Accumulate token-global settlement fee elsewhere, claim fee first, then withdraw | Lender | Custody covers all liabilities | Formal solvency claims defense; runtime test still valuable | `PoC_Blackbox_CrossMarketAggregateAccounting.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:17:| BL-008 | Fee claims cannot borrow backing from another market | `claimSettlementFee`, `claimContinuousFee` | Same loan token markets, interleave claims and withdrawals | Lenders | Aggregate liabilities remain backed | May be formally proven | Aggregate claim ordering test |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:18:| BL-009 | Market creation is isolated to users selecting that market | `touchMarket`, bundles | Route a delegated user through attacker-selected market | Delegated user | Bad market requires explicit consent | Broad delegation likely intended | `PoC_Blackbox_PermissionlessMarketContamination.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:19:| BL-010 | Oracle/gate risk remains market-local | `isHealthy`, `liquidate`, bundles | Mix shared actor authorization with malicious gated market route | Lender or borrower | Chosen risk cannot contaminate unrelated position | Must prove missing consent | Consent-boundary PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:20:| BL-011 | Fee setter changes only stale quote fillability | `setMarketSettlementFee`, bundles | Quote route, change fee, force different valid fallback debt profile | Route user | Slippage arguments bound changed economics | Duplicate if only stale quote revert | `PoC_Blackbox_QuoteSettlementMismatch.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:21:| BL-012 | Maturity changes only allowed liquidation mode | `take`, `liquidate`, bundles | Prepare route before maturity, settle after maturity with debt-reducing and debt-increasing legs | Borrower | Post-maturity exposure cannot increase | Existing direct maturity tests narrow | Maturity route PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:22:| BL-013 | RCF threshold is only gas-policy relief | `liquidate` | Construct just-under/over threshold state and compare full liquidation | Borrower, lenders | Tiny threshold delta cannot create material avoidable loss | Could be intended parameter risk | RCF discontinuity PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:23:| BL-014 | Liquidators cannot rationally choose a path that increases lender loss beyond disclosed incentives | `liquidate` multi-collateral | Choose collateral order with different `maxLif` and leave bad-debt realization state | Lenders | Equivalent liquidation paths do not create avoidable social loss | Preference is documented; require material exploit | Multi-collateral order PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:24:| BL-015 | Active collateral can be safely added before debt | `supplyCollateral`, `take` | Activate liveness-hostile collateral while debtless, then route debt into account | Borrower | Debt entry requires consent to all active risks | Borrower may have consented | Route-forced debt PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:25:| BL-016 | Authorization revocation stops future economic effects | `setIsAuthorized`, `EcrecoverAuthorizer`, ratifiers | Combine pre-signed authorization and separate route after revocation ordering | Authorizer | Revocation effect matches signed intent | Broad delegated authority documented | `PoC_Blackbox_AuthorizationIntentSplit.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:26:| BL-017 | Signed authorization has one obvious action class | `EcrecoverAuthorizer.setIsAuthorized` | Use newly authorized actor across core, bundler, and ratifier reuse surfaces | Authorizer | Signature effect scope is explicit | Likely intended broad core auth | Scope-composition PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:27:| BL-018 | Ratifier signer authority reflects offer-maker intent at fill time | `EcrecoverRatifier.isRatified` | Revoke signer in one surface while another authorization chain remains valid | Maker | Revoked signer cannot indirectly validate offer | Duplicate if plain delegate grief | Chained-auth PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:28:| BL-019 | Route fallback is economically interchangeable | bundle loops | Make first offer fail for non-price reason so valid fallback opens different exposure | Taker | Explicit bounds capture fallback economics | Likely intended skip semantics | Route side-effect PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:29:| BL-020 | Route builder cannot collect a fee without delivering intended action | bundles referral | Use fallback and rounding threshold to satisfy token target with unexpected units | User | Referral paid only for bounded action | Existing referral tests narrow | Route-average-price PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:30:| BL-021 | Settlement fees are always cash-backed at claim time | `take`, `claimSettlementFee` | Compose same-token markets and same-transaction claims after fee accrual | Fee claimer, lenders | Claimable fees never use lender backing | Admin-only claimer, but solvency impact can affect lenders | Aggregate custody PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:31:| BL-022 | Continuous-fee claim cannot front-run lazy lender synchronization | `updatePosition`, `claimContinuousFee`, `withdraw` | Accrue lazy fee, repay, claim and withdraw in alternate orders | Lenders | Claimed fee is reserved once | Prior composition covers one market; test multi-market | Deferred fee PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:32:| BL-023 | A borrower with debt cannot escape oracle-dependent health checks | `withdrawCollateral`, `take` | Use repay-to-zero and collateral withdrawal in one bundle around quote transition | Lenders | Collateral exit only after debt is repaid | Likely correct | Bundle repay exit test |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:33:| BL-024 | Per-market IDs isolate all state but shared custody | `toId`, token balance | Alternate valid claims across same-token markets | Lenders | Sum of claims is backed | Distinct from formal aliasing | Aggregate accounting invariant |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:34:| BL-025 | Event stream lets monitoring reconstruct actionable solvency | `EventsLib`, lazy accrual | Replay events across repay, slash, touch, claim, withdraw | Lenders, monitors | Event mirror equals storage-relevant state | P3 unless delayed action creates loss | `PoC_Blackbox_EventStorageMismatch.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:35:| BL-026 | Loss-factor rounding remains dust-only | `liquidate`, `updatePosition` | Repeated small defaults until threshold flips claim or health branch | Lenders | Dust cannot trigger non-dust branch | Duplicate unless branch flip | `PoC_Blackbox_DustToNonDustStateFlip.sol` |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:36:| BL-027 | Zero-unit actions are harmless outside callbacks | `repay`, `withdraw`, bundles | Use zero amounts to trigger market creation, approval, or route-selected side effects | User | No-op cannot create third-party economic effect | Direct zero callback replay closed | Zero-path PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:37:| BL-028 | A market creator cannot influence unrelated indexer identity | `MarketCreated`, `toMarket` | Create similar markets differing only in peripheral risk params | UI user | Indexer displays full consent tuple | Runtime core likely safe; UI-dependent | Event identity replay |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:38:| BL-029 | Permissionless update calls help, not harm, stale lenders | `updatePosition` | Force touch before lender-planned withdrawal or rollover | Lender | Public touch cannot worsen exit beyond accrued economics | Likely intended crystallization | Forced-touch PoC |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:39:| BL-030 | Lender rollover race is disclosed and bounded | `take`, `withdrawable` | Resting sell offer rolls realized cash into new borrower risk before lender withdraws | Lender | Lender consent to rollover is explicit | Blackthorn L-15 duplicate-risk | Dedup-only unless new periphery path |
audits/asyam/workflow/blackboxLogicHunt/02_BUSINESS_LOGIC_ATTACKS.md:43:Start with BL-001, BL-002, BL-003, BL-007, BL-016, BL-021, and BL-026. The others are filters and fallback queues.
